350176.d: Skill Category 1: Comprehend written, audio, audiovisual, and visual text (text, pictures, and numbers).

350177.d: Skill 1.A: Describe the literal meaning of the text.

350180.d: 1.A.3: Retell or summarize information in narrative form.

350183.d: 1.B.1: Identify and describe patterns and trends in data.

350184.d: 1.B.2: Describe data from a table, chart, graph, map, or infographic.

350185.d: Skill Category 2: Make interdisciplinary and cultural connections.

350187.d: 2.A.1: Identify and/or describe content and connections among cultural topics.

350188.d: 2.A.2: Explain how data from a graph or table illustrate cultural topics or phenomena.

350189.d: 2.A.3: Explain how information from a text connects or relates to the target cultural topics or phenomena.

350190.d: 2.A.4: Infer cultural information from a text.

350191.d: Skill 2.B: Make connections in and across disciplines.

350192.d: 2.B.1: Identify and/or describe content and connections among interdisciplinary topics.

350193.d: 2.B.2: Explain how data from a graph or table illustrate interdisciplinary topics or phenomena.

350194.d: 2.B.3: Explain how information from a text connects or relates to interdisciplinary topics or phenomena.

350195.d: 2.B.4: Infer interdisciplinary information from a text.

350196.d: Skill Category 3: Interpret the content of written or audio text (words).

350197.d: Skill 3.A: Interpret the distinguishing features of a text.

350200.d: 3.A.3: Identify and/or describe the point(s) of view, perspective(s), tone or attitude.

350201.d: 3.A.4: Identify organizing and/or rhetorical structures and/or strategies.

350202.d: Skill 3.B: Interpret the meaning of a text.

350203.d: 3.B.1: Identify and/or describe similarities and/or differences among different types of texts.

350205.d: Skill Category 4: Make meanings from words and expressions.

350206.d: Skill 4.A: Determine the meaning of familiar and unfamiliar words.

350207.d: 4.A.1: Determine the meaning of a variety of vocabulary.

350208.d: 4.A.2: Deduce the meaning of unfamiliar words or expressions.

350209.d: Skill 4.B: Use words appropriate for a given context.

350210.d: 4.B.1: Use a variety of vocabulary in written and spoken communication.

350211.d: 4.B.2: Explain and use idiomatic and culturally authentic expressions.

350212.d: Skill Category 5: Communicate interpersonally by speaking with others.

350213.d: Skill 5.A: Understand and apply appropriate communication strategies in interpersonal speaking.

350214.d: 5.A.1: Initiate, maintain, and close spoken exchanges.

350215.d: 5.A.2: Comprehend a spoken interlocutor's message in spoken exchanges.

350216.d: 5.A.3: Provide and obtain relevant information in spoken exchanges.

350217.d: 5.A.4: Use appropriate register and greeting for the intended target culture audience in spoken exchanges.

350218.d: 5.A.5: Use pronunciation that is comprehensible when interacting with speakers of the target language in spoken exchanges.

350219.d: 5.A.6: Use effective intonation patterns, pacing, and delivery when interacting with speakers of the target language in spoken exchanges.

350220.d: 5.A.7: Use communication strategies, such as circumlocution, requesting clarification, asking for repetition, and paraphrasing to maintain spoken exchanges.

350221.d: Skill 5.B: Understand and apply appropriate and varied syntactical expressions in interpersonal speaking.

350222.d: 5.B.1: Use a variety of grammar and syntax in spoken exchanges.

350223.d: 5.B.2: Use transitional expressions and cohesive devices in spoken exchanges.

350224.d: 5.B.3: Comprehend and produce simple, compound, and complex sentences in a variety of time frames in spoken exchanges.

350225.d: 5.B.4: Monitor language production; recognize errors and attempt self-correction in spoken exchanges.

350226.d: Skill Category 6: Communicate interpersonally by writing to others.

350227.d: Skill 6.A: Understand and apply appropriate communication strategies in interpersonal writing.

350228.d: 6.A.1: Initiate, maintain, and close written exchanges.

350229.d: 6.A.2: Provide and obtain relevant information in written exchanges.

350230.d: 6.A.3: Use a variety of grammar and syntax in written exchanges.

350231.d: 6.A.4: Use register appropriate for the intended target culture audience in written exchanges.

350232.d: 6.A.5: Use communication strategies, such as circumlocution, requesting clarification, and paraphrasing to maintain written exchanges.

350233.d: Skill 6.B: Understand and apply appropriate and varied syntactical expressions in interpersonal writing.

350234.d: 6.B.1: Use transitional expressions and cohesive devices to create paragraph length discourse in written exchanges.

350235.d: 6.B.2: Comprehend and produce simple, compound, and complex sentences in a variety of time frames in written exchanges.

350236.d: 6.B.3: Use standard conventions of the written language (e.g., capitalization, orthography, accents, punctuation) in written exchanges.

350237.d: 6.B.4: Monitor language production; recognize errors and attempt self-correction written exchanges.

350241.d: 7.A.2: Use research strategies to gather information and evidence for inclusion in spoken presentations.

350246.d: 7.B.4: Use effective intonation patterns, pacing, and delivery in spoken presentations.
